</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/4/03 2:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=742.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Towards a new Malevolence</span><hr size=1> The halls were silent as many slept within them, the faint sounds of their nocturnal breathing not audible beyond the heavy wooden doors of the comrade's quarters. Unable to sleep, she clicked open the latch on her door, stepping lightly into the hallway. She began to pace, many thoughts scrambling to dominate her mind.<br>
<br>
Malevolent Desires, founded on one principle, the sanctity of darkness. Dedicated to all things wicked. Its one purpose, to obliterate the light. It had begun easily enough, many coming together towards the common goal. However, somewhere along the way, they faltered.<br>
<br>
Many succumbed to outside influences, choosing to sleep in the dark void of an alternate reality. Some felt they were not 'needed' enough and chose to depart. Yet others found themselves wandering, looking for what they could not seek to find within the army. <br>
<br>
And yet, they perservered. <br>
<br>
Continuing to pace, she bit her lower lip, lost in deep thought as she struggled to find a solution to the dilemma before her. The words of the Ogre, Targok, echoed in her mind.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Ta fite gud ya gotta be kwik, ya think long time, ya git dead. Ya eeder move first, or ya move last. Ain' nobudee like ta be last. Yuh, sumbudee got da first move, so ya gotta make yers reel gud so dem don' git anudder.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
She shook her head, a smile playing about her lips for the first time that evening. Though her thoughts were dark, she could not help but be amused that such words of wisdom came from one others dismissed with little regard. Such was often the case, she had discovered. A most fatal error, to discount someone.. to underestimate your allies, your foes. She hoped to never fall victim to such disallowance.<br>
<br>
The silence of the Inn was almost unbearable. The air seemed thick with it.. hard to breathe. And yet, she paced onward, her mind awash with possibilities. She knew what she wanted.. how to achieve it? How to make that first move, that move the Ogre had told her was necessary in any battle? He had not known what battle Persephoria faced, and yet his words were fitting all the same.<br>
<br>
She knew then, suddenly, exactly what she must do. She turned on her heel, almost running back to her room to find a scrap of parchment. To pull her seashell quill from its perch and dip it once again into the crimson ink. <br>
<br>
It's not over 'til it's over. And, if she had her way, it would never be over.<br>
<br>
