<br>
It was soon forthcoming, sooner than she had expected. Her hand trembled as she twisted the knob to her door, allowing the ghoulish courier to lurch its way inside, holding a tattered piece of parchment tightly in its grasp. She pulled the bit of paper from it, her eyes quickly going to the familiar handwriting, scanning it once. The message contained within weakened her knees, stopped her heart. She leaned her back against the door, sliding along its length until she sat on the floor, where she read the missive in depth.<br>
<br>
Unbidden tears welled in her eyes and then spilled over, dropping onto the parchment, marring the ink, soaking into the paper. The enormity of what was to come overwhelmed her, the shock taking her very breath from her.<br>
<br>
Evani wasn't coming back.<br>
<br>
She must lead the army now.<br>
